name: job-id
description: The ID of the job that scheduled the run

name: run-id
description: The ID of the run this result row should be associated with

name: run-status
description: The status of the run this result row should be associated with

name: grid-filter
description: Text for a grid identifer or a pattern to filter the sensor grids of the model that are simulated. For instance, first_floor_* will simulate only the sensor grids that have an identifier that starts with first_floor_. By default, all grids in the model will be simulated.

alias.name: grid_filter
alias.description: Text for a grid identifer or a pattern to filter the sensor grids of the model that are simulated. For instance, first_floor_* will simulate only the sensor grids that have an identifier that starts with first_floor_. By default, all grids in the model will be simulated.

name: model
description: A Honeybee model in HBJSON file format.

alias.name: model
alias.description: A Honeybee Model to simulate or the path to a HBJSON file of a Model. This can also be the path to a HBpkl file, though this is only recommended for cases where the model is extremely large.

alias.name: model
alias.description: This input links the model to Rhino model.

name: radiance-parameters
description: The radiance parameters for ray tracing

alias.name: radiance_par
alias.description: Text for the radiance parameters to be used for ray tracing. (Default: -ab 2 -aa 0.1 -ad 2048 -ar 64).

name: sensor-count
description: The maximum number of grid points per parallel execution

alias.name: sensor_count
alias.description: Positive integer for the number of sensor grid points per parallel execution. Lower numbers will result in sensor grids being split into more pieces and, since each grid piece is run by a separate worker, this can mean a faster simulation on machines with several CPUs. However ,If the number is too low, the overhad of splitting the grid will not be worth the time gained through parallelization. (Default: 200).

name: results
description: Folder with raw result files (.res) that contain daylight factor values for each sensor.

alias.description: Text for the radiance parameters to be used for ray tracing. (Default: -ab 2 -aa 0.1 -ad 2048 -ar 64).

name: sensor-count
description: The maximum number of grid points per parallel execution

alias.name: sensor_count
alias.description: Positive integer for the number of sensor grid points per parallel execution. Lower numbers will result in sensor grids being split into more pieces and, since each grid piece is run by a separate worker, this can mean a faster simulation on machines with several CPUs. However ,If the number is too low, the overhad of splitting the grid will not be worth the time gained through parallelization. (Default: 200).
